Julian Bond, a civil rights leader and friend of President Obama, has passed away. Bond dedicated his life to justice and equality, serving as the leader of the Student Nonviolent Coordinating Committee, co-founding the Southern Poverty Law Center, and playing a key role in the Georgia legislature and NAACP. The President and First Lady have been inspired by Bond's example and express their condolences to his family. Bond's legacy is one of positive change for the country.